  "text": "In the present study, we examined whether cyclic electron flow within PSII functions in intact chloroplasts that cannot fix CO 2 . A DpH across the thylakoid membranes is required for CEF-PSII activity [CITATION_1] . Nigericin, a protonophore, lowered the electron flux in PSII, but enhanced the linear electron flow in intact chloroplasts as determined by the Fig. 3 Dependence of the relative electron fluxes in PSII attributable to WWC and CEF-PSII on light intensity. The relative electron fluxes in PSII attributable to WWC and CEF-PSII, .(PSII)(+DpH, WWC) Ṕ FD and .(PSII)(+DpH, CEF-PSII) ´ PFD, were calculated from the data in Fig. 2 , as described in the text, and plotted against light intensity. Circles, .(PSII)(+DpH, WWC) ´ PFD; Diamonds, .(PSII) (+DpH, CEF-PSII) ´ PFD. The insert shows the dependence of the formation of DpH across thylakoid membranes on light intensity. The reaction mixture was the same as in Fig. 1A , except for the addition of 9-aminoacridine of 2 mM. Fluorescence of 9-aminoacridine was measured with excitation by xenon flashes at 16 Hz, and formation of DpH by actinic red light with several intensities was determined from its quenching.",
